text: for eight solid years of my life from
age 16 until 24 I was partying non-stop
sometimes too hard my four years
attending one of the biggest party
colleges in the world the University of
wisconsin-madison was some of the best
years of my life
there wasn't a single Thursday Friday or
Saturday night that we weren't out at a
bar or a concert or a house party until
3:00 a.m. and then I studied abroad in
Prague Czech Republic in 2012 which was
probably the peak of my party hood I'm
not exaggerating when I tell you that I
was out on the town six nights a week
for four months straight this was also
when I got hooked on EDM and going to
dance music festivals where I proceeded
to hit 15 plus accesible around the
world in my early 20s when I graduated
college I moved to South Korea to teach
English for two years and believe it or
not Seoul is like another planet when it
comes to nightlife nobody else can
compete with Koreans and their binge for
drinking and staying out all night while
in Korea I started my first travel blog
called the hungry partier which hence
the name was a place for me to share my
crazy drug and party stories around the
world however that blog no longer exists
which you are about to find out why fast
forward to 2018 I'm 26 years old and I
get drunk off two beers I occasionally
go out a beer here a beer there or
sometimes more when I'm with old friends
but I'm certainly not the hungry partier
I once was did I just grow up or did I
get sick of partying well neither really
perhaps getting in a serious
relationship is part of the picture but
the real reason I gave up partying is
because it's a waste of time and money
nowadays I use all that money that I
used to spend on beer and raves for
flights and experiences like this this
and this taking my girlfriend on dates
is a lot more enjoyable than raging in a
nightclub
instead of being hungover all day I wake
up at the crack of dawn to get views
like this like this and like this
without alcohol
I could stay more focused on making
daily travel videos which is my passion
and my future but I do not regret any
part of my path those parties and
memories are something I'll cherish
forever and they have made me who I am
today but as for now I'm much happier
and successful away from the booze I'm
driven ski and if you like my travel
videos please click Subscribe and join
me as I plan to visit every country in
the world
